PART II: CHAT GUARD SPECIFIC LICENCE TERMS

1. DEFINITIONS

1.1 "Chat Guard" shall mean the software and services provided by the Licensor under the trade name
Chat Guard, including all associated code, documentation, updates, and modifications thereto,
designed to enhance security and moderation functionalities within Discord servers.

1.2 "Creative Commons Licence" shall mean the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike
4.0 International Public Licence, as set forth in Part I of this Agreement, and published at
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode.

1.3 "Licensee" shall mean any individual, corporation, partnership, or other entity that accesses
or uses Chat Guard in accordance with this Agreement.

1.4 "Discord" shall mean the communication platform operated by Discord Inc., on which Chat Guard
is designed to function.

1.5 "Intellectual Property Rights" shall mean all copyrights, trademarks, patents, trade secrets,
and any other proprietary rights recognised under the laws of the United Kingdom or any other
jurisdiction, pertaining to Chat Guard.

2. GRANT OF LICENCE

2.1 Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the Creative Commons Licence, the
Licensor hereby grants to the Licensee a worldwide, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable
licence to use, copy, modify, and distribute Chat Guard, provided that:

(a) The Licensee attributes appropriate credit to the Licensor, including but not limited to
referencing "Chat Guard © 2025 by HMD Developments, Inc." in any reproduction, distribution, or
derivative work;

(b) The Licensee does not use Chat Guard for any commercial purposes, as defined under the Creative
Commons Licence;

(c) Any derivative works created by the Licensee are licensed under identical terms, as stipulated
by the ShareAlike provision of the Creative Commons Licence;

(d) The Licensee complies fully with all terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, the
Creative Commons Licence, and the Discord Terms of Service.

2.2 The licence granted herein does not confer upon the Licensee any ownership rights in Chat Guard
or any Intellectual Property Rights therein, all of which remain vested exclusively in the
Licensor.

3. RESTRICTIONS ON USE

3.1 The Licensee shall not, under any circumstances:

(a) Use Chat Guard in any manner that violates the Discord Terms of Service, the Creative Commons
Licence, or any applicable laws or regulations;

(b) Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise derive the source code of
Chat Guard, except to the extent expressly permitted by applicable law;

(c) Exploit any vulnerabilities in Chat Guard or engage in any activity that may harm Chat Guard,
its users, or its operational integrity;

(d) Misuse or abuse Chat Guard’s protection systems, including but not limited to circumvention or
manipulation thereof;

(e) Use Chat Guard to harass, disrupt, or otherwise interfere with the experience of other users or
servers;

(f) Sublicense, assign, or transfer this Agreement or any rights granted hereunder to any third
party without the prior written consent of the Licensor.

4. DATA COLLECTION AND PRIVACY

4.1 The Licensee acknowledges and agrees that Chat Guard may collect and store certain data as
outlined in the Chat Guard Privacy Policy, last updated on 6th May 2025, including but not limited
to User IDs, Server IDs, Whitelisted IDs, and Log Channel IDs, as necessary for the operation of
the service.

4.2 The Licensee further acknowledges that direct messages sent to Chat Guard are not stored, and
the Licensee is advised not to share sensitive information via such messages.

4.3 The Licensee may request deletion of their data by submitting a formal request to
legal@hmddevs.org, which shall be processed within thirty (30) business days, subject to identity
verification by the Licensor.

5. TERMS OF USE AND COMPLIANCE

5.1 The Licensee agrees to comply fully with the Chat Guard Terms of Use, last updated on 6th May
2025, which form an integral part of this Agreement. Any violation of the Terms of Use shall
constitute a material breach of this Agreement.

5.2 In the event of a violation, the Licensor reserves the right to suspend or terminate the
Licensee’s access to Chat Guard, including potential inclusion in the Chat Guard Blacklist system,
with or without notice.

5.3 The Licensee may appeal any penalties imposed by submitting a formal request to
legal@hmddevs.org, which shall be reviewed within thirty (30) business days, with the Licensor
retaining sole discretion over the outcome.

6. TERMINATION

6.1 This Agreement and the licence granted herein may be terminated by the Licensor at its sole
discretion, with or without cause, upon written notice to the Licensee.

6.2 Upon termination, the Licensee shall immediately cease all use of Chat Guard and destroy or
return to the Licensor any copies thereof in their possession or control.

6.3 The provisions of Sections 1, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10 of Part II, and Sections 1, 5, 6, 7, and
8 of Part I, shall survive the termination of this Agreement for any reason.

